Traub revealed the news that Shiver are producing&nbsp;Mortal Kombat 11&nbsp;at the same time as NetherRealm work on the other console editions, &quot;So it's sort of a co-development&quot;, he explained. Traub was asked about the Switch edition being a downgrade, to which he replied that &quot;Special geometry reductions&quot; were being implemented to ensure a smooth experience for Nintendo's&nbsp;MK&nbsp;fanbase.<br />
<br />
He did note, however, that it&rsquo;s still &ldquo;really fantastic.&rdquo;
